thread.title: Japan's ANA 9-month profit jumps 27.4 pct

author: Reuters Editorial
title: Japan's ANA 9-month profit jumps 27.4 pct
text:
TOKYO, Feb 1 (Reuters) - ANA Holdings Inc, Japanâ€™s biggest airline by revenue, posted a 27.4 percent rise in operating profit in the nine months to December as economic growth boosted travel demand.
Profit for the nine months was 165.97 billion yen ($1.52 billion), up from 130.23 yen in the same period a year earlier.
ANA maintained its forecast that operating profit for the year to March would hit 160 billion yen.
$1 = 109.3500 yen Reporting by Minami Funakoshi; Editing by Jacqueline Wong
